item.title: Latest snapshot of the coronavirus impact
Bondi waters busy as iconic beach reopens
item.description: Hundreds of surfers have returned to the water at Bondi for the first time since the beach was closed five weeks ago due to COVID-19 restrictions.

item.title: Economic virus shock outspeeds depression
item.description: The economic shock of coronavirus in Australia has smashed jobs and businesses faster than the Great Depression.

item.title: Lendlease raising $1.1b in share sale
item.description: LendLease Group aims to raise about $1.15 billion to guard against market uncertainty brought about by the coronavirus outbreak and has withdrawn all forecasts provided with its first-half results.

item.title: Labor MP Mike Kelly may retire within days
item.description: Labor MP Mike Kelly is expected to retire from federal parliament within days, triggering a by-election in the marginal NSW electorate of Eden-Monaro.

item.title: Greens square up again for Trad’s seat
item.description: A Greens candidate who almost toppled Queensland's treasurer three years ago is squaring up for a second tilt at the South Brisbane seat.

item.title: High living costs spark Lebanon protests
item.description: The facades of several banks have been smashed with at least one set on fire as protests fuelled by Lebanon's economic crisis turned violent in the northern city of Tripoli.

item.title: NSW fast-tracks projects to boost economy
item.description: The first tranche of NSW construction projects set to be fast-tracked in the wake of the COVID-19 pandemic will create thousands of jobs and inject more than $7 billion into the state's economy.

item.title: Coronavirus restriction changes by state
item.description: WHICH STATES AND TERRITORIES ARE EASING CORONAVIRUS RESTRICTIONS?

item.title: China threat inappropriate: trade minister
item.description: Australia's trade minister has declared the country won't give in to coercion after China threatened to withdraw support from the nation's major export industries.
